# MinOS — Project Summary & Architecture

> A minimal Linux-based OS built from scratch in C, designed to run **containerized workloads** using Linux namespaces, cgroups v2, seccomp, and a custom supervisor.

---

## Project Overview

MinOS is a hand-built operating system that boots a custom Linux kernel, runs its own `init` as PID 1, manages services via a custom supervisor, and supports lightweight container execution via `minc` — its own Docker-like container runtime. It targets QEMU/KVM and produces a bootable disk image (`myos.img`).

---

