## Boot Sequence

```
BIOS/UEFI
  └─► Syslinux (syslinux/syslinux.cfg)
        └─► Linux Kernel (kernel/bzImage) + stage-1 initramfs
              └─► initramfs-stage1/init  (shell script)
                    1. Mounts /proc, /sys, /dev
                    2. Detects vda1 (ext4) + vda2 (squashfs)
                    3. Mounts squashfs → /squash
                    4. Mounts overlay (squashfs lower + ext4 upper) → /newroot
                    5. switch_root /newroot /sbin/init
                          └─► init/main.c  (PID 1, C binary)
                                1. mount_filesystems() → proc/sys/dev/tmp/cgroup2
                                2. setup_signals()
                                3. start_supervisor() → exec /supervisor /services.d
                                      └─► supervisor/main.c
                                            ├─ Loads services from /services.d/*.conf
                                            ├─ Spawns: cgmgr, netd, console (/bin/sh)
                                            └─ Monitors + restarts services on crash
                                4. reaper loop (waitpid)
```

---

## Component Deep-Dives

### `init` (PID 1)
- Written in C; runs as PID 1
- Mounts all virtual filesystems including **cgroup v2** at `/sys/fs/cgroup`
- Enables `cpu`, `pids`, and `memory` controllers at the root cgroup
- Creates `/sys/fs/cgroup/system` and `/sys/fs/cgroup/containers` slices
- Forks the supervisor, then loops reaping zombie processes

### `supervisor`
- Reads `.conf` files from `/services.d/` (key=value format)
- Supports 3 restart policies: `always`, `on-failure`, `never`
- Exponential backoff on restarts: 1s → 2s → 4s → 8s → 16s → 30s cap
- Manages up to 32 services
- Services at startup: `cgmgr`, `netd`, `console` (shell)

### `minc` — Container Runtime
- CLI: `minc run [-t] <binary> [args...]`
- `-t` flag allocates a controlling terminal (for interactive shells)
- Generates incremental container IDs: `c0`, `c1`, `c2`, ...
- Uses `clone()` with namespace flags:
  - `CLONE_NEWPID` — own PID tree (container's process = PID 1)
  - `CLONE_NEWNS` — own mount namespace (can remount `/proc`)
  - `CLONE_NEWUTS` — own hostname (`sethostname(id)`)
- Assigns container to a cgroup via `cgroup.procs`
- Sets `cpu.weight` and `pids.max` per container
- Installs **seccomp BPF whitelist** before `execv()`
- Uses a **sync pipe** so child waits until cgroup assignment is done

### `netd` — Network Daemon
- Runs once at boot, then exits cleanly (`restart=on-failure`)
- Creates host bridge `osBr0` at `10.0.0.1/24`
- Enables IP forwarding (`/proc/sys/net/ipv4/ip_forward`)
- Sets up NAT/masquerade for container internet access
- Config: `net.conf` (bridge name, IP, prefix, outbound interface)
- Per-container veth pairs created by `runtime/spawn.c` (not yet connected)

### `cgmgr` — Cgroup Manager
- Runs once at boot, exits cleanly
- Enables `cpu`, `pids`, `memory` controllers on root and `containers/`
- Reads `slices.conf` and applies `cpu.weight` + `memory.max` to each slice
- Default slices:
  - `system`: cpu_weight=200, mem_max=512M
  - `containers`: cpu_weight=800, mem_max=2G

### `seccomp` — Syscall Filter
- Raw BPF filter (no `libseccomp` dependency)
- Architecture check first (kills process on wrong arch — prevents 32-bit bypass)
- Whitelist of ~80 syscalls: I/O, file ops, process, memory, signals, time, networking, epoll
- Default action: `EPERM` (returns error, doesn't kill — allows graceful failure)

---

## Key Configs

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `cgroup/slices.conf` | CPU + memory limits for `system` and `containers` cgroup slices |
| `netd/net.conf` | Bridge name, IP, prefix, outbound interface, container IP pool |
| `rootfs/services.d/console.conf` | Spawns `/bin/sh` terminal as a service |
| `syslinux/syslinux.cfg` | Bootloader config — kernel cmdline |

---

## Build System

```bash
make all       # compile init + daemons + tools + disk image
make kernel    # (manual: cd kernel && make bzImage -j$(nproc))
make init      # compile PID 1 init binary
make daemons   # compile supervisor, cgmgr, netd, minc
make tools     # compile cginspect, nslist
make image     # pack squashfs + assemble disk image
make test      # boot in QEMU, tee output to build/boot.log
make verify    # run automated boot verification suite
make clean     # remove all generated files
```

**Toolchain:** `gcc -static -O2` (all binaries statically linked — no libc.so needed at runtime)

---

## Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Kernel | Custom-configured Linux (`kernel/config`) |
| Bootloader | Syslinux |
| Root Filesystem | SquashFS (read-only) + OverlayFS (persistent writes on ext4) |
| Init System | Custom C (`init/`) |
| Service Manager | Custom C (`supervisor/`) |
| Container Runtime | Custom C (`runtime/`) — `clone()` + cgroup v2 |
| Networking | Netlink bridge + nftables NAT (`netd/`) |
| Resource Control | cgroup v2 (`cgroup/`) |
| Security | BPF seccomp whitelist (`runtime/seccomp.c`) |
| Userland | BusyBox (statically linked) |
| Emulator | QEMU/KVM (`build/qemu.sh`) |
| Build | GNU Make + shell scripts |
